As observational evidence implies that we live in a universe with a nonzero (albeit tiny), \textit{positive} vacuum energy density, one can envision a spandex fabric with a negative areal mass density when the conceptual analogy of particle orbits in general relativity and rolling marble orbits on a warped spandex fabric is employed.  This fictional spandex fabric would feel a repulsive force from the uniform gravitational field of the earth and tend to hang \textit{up} towards the ceiling rather than down towards the floor.  

This contribution to the total warping of the spandex surface gives rise to a repulsive force on the orbiting marble, effectively competing with the attractive force of the central mass contribution.  







